channel.title: Compiler problem JDK 6 update 16
channel.description:
I currently have JDK 6 update 16 on my PC I'm trying to compile my server and i keep getting this "system could not find the path specified"
I've asked my friend if he had the same java he said yes and his compiler worked so i asked him to give me the notepad i copy pasted into the compiler and still get the same message
please help me Thanks

in your local disk c folder is there a sun folder? if so click it go to sdk jdk bin then copy that and paste it.

so it should look like your old one but with different paths.
